{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MwHNuwFfZTPHaNpRSfJVLr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Self-Evolution System Design\n     2→\n     3→## Overview\n     4→\n     5→Cloche's self-evolution system analyzes workflow run history and user feedback to\n     6→automatically improve prompts, add validation steps, and refine workflows over\n     7→time. It is a daemon-side post-run pipeline that triggers after every workflow\n     8→completion, applies changes directly to project files, and maintains a structured\n     9→audit trail.\n    10→\n    11→The system draws on the ACE (Agentic Context Engineering) framework for prompt\n    12→evolution — treating prompts as structured, itemized playbooks that accumulate\n    13→lessons rather than monolithic documents that get rewritten.\n    14→\n    15→**Scope (this version):** Additive changes only. Prompt updates, new script\n    16→steps, new agent steps, new wiring. No step removal or mutation of existing step\n    17→definitions.\n    18→\n    19→## Architecture\n    20→\n    21→The evolution system is a multi-stage pipeline with three specialized output\n    22→branches. The LLM handles classification, reflection, and content generation.\n    23→Deterministic Go code handles structural manipulation (DSL editing, file I/O,\n    24→audit logging).\n    25→\n    26→```\n    27→                    ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n    28→                    │         Workflow Run Completes       │\n    29→                    └──────────────┬──────────────────────┘\n    30→                                   │\n    31→                    ┌──────────────▼──────────────────────┐\n    32→                    │           Collector                  │\n    33→                    │  Gathers: run results, history.log,  │\n    34→                    │  step outputs, knowledge base,       │\n    35→                    │  current prompts + workflow          │\n    36→                    └──────────────┬──────────────────────┘\n    37→                                   │\n    38→                    ┌──────────────▼──────────────────────┐\n    39→                    │         Classifier (LLM)            │\n    40→                    │  Categorizes run prompt:             │\n    41→                    │  bug | feedback | feature |          │\n    42→                    │  enhancement | chore                 │\n    43→                    └──────────────┬──────────────────────┘\n    44→                                   │\n    45→                    ┌──────────────▼──────────────────────┐\n    46→                    │         Reflector (LLM)              │\n    47→                    │  ACE-style: examines traces,         │\n    48→                    │  extracts structured lessons          │\n    49→                    │  (bullets with metadata)              │\n    50→                    └──────────────┬──────────────────────┘\n    51→                                   │\n    52→              ┌────────────────────┼────────────────────┐\n    53→              │                    │                     │\n    54→   ┌──────────▼────────┐ ┌────────▼──────────┐ ┌───────▼──────────┐\n    55→   │  Prompt Curator    │ │  Script Generator │ │  DSL Mutator     │\n    56→   │  (LLM + dedup)     │ │  (LLM)            │ │  (Go code)       │\n    57→   │                    │ │                    │ │                   │\n    58→   │  Merges lessons    │ │  Writes new        │ │  Adds steps,     │\n    59→   │  into prompt files │ │  checker/linter    │ │  wiring, collects │\n    60→   │  as structured     │ │  scripts           │ │  to .cloche file  │\n    61→   │  bullets           │ │                    │ │                   │\n    62→   └────────┬───────────┘ └────────┬───────────┘ └───────┬──────────┘\n    63→            │                      │                      │\n    64→            └──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┘\n    65→                                   │\n    66→                    ┌──────────────▼──────────────────────┐\n    67→                    │         Audit Logger                 │\n    68→                    │  Records all changes + reasons        │\n    69→                    │  Updates knowledge base summary       │\n    70→                    │  Snapshots pre-change state           │\n    71→                    └─────────────────────────────────────┘\n    72→```\n    73→\n    74→The three branches fire independently based on lesson category. A single\n    75→evolution pass may produce changes across multiple branches, or none at all.\n    76→\n    77→## Multi-Project Scoping\n    78→\n    79→The daemon supports multiple concurrent cloche instances across different\n    80→projects (and multiple runs within the same project). Every run record includes\n    81→`project_dir` — the absolute path to the project directory where `cloche run`\n    82→was invoked.\n    83→\n    84→All evolution state is scoped by project_dir + workflow_name:\n    85→- SQLite queries filter by project_dir\n    86→- Knowledge bases live at `<project_dir>/.cloche/evolution/knowledge/<workflow>.md`\n    87→- Evolution passes for different projects/workflows run independently\n    88→- One evolution pass at a time per project+workflow (mutex)\n    89→\n    90→## Data Collection\n    91→\n    92→### New Signals Captured Per Run\n    93→\n    94→| Signal               | Where captured                        | Notes                          |\n    95→|----------------------|---------------------------------------|--------------------------------|\n    96→| Assembled prompt     | Prompt adapter, before LLM invocation | Full text sent to the agent    |\n    97→| Agent stdout         | Prompt adapter, after agent returns   | Full LLM response              |\n    98→| Run prompt class     | Classifier LLM, post-run             | bug/feedback/feature/etc.      |\n    99→| Retry count per step | Prompt adapter attempt tracking       | Already in filesystem, add to SQLite |\n   100→| Project directory    | CLI sends to daemon via gRPC          | Currently implicit             |\n   101→\n   102→### Run Prompt Classification\n   103→\n   104→The Classifier examines each run's `--prompt` text and categorizes it:\n   105→\n   106→- **bug** — fixing something broken; indicates a gap the system should reflect on\n   107→  for patterns in its approach to software development\n   108→- **feedback** — code review style issues (DRY, SOLID, architecture); things\n   109→  caught in a typical review cycle that the system should watch its output for\n   110→- **feature** — new functionality; normal work\n   111→- **enhancement** — improving existing functionality\n   112→- **chore** — maintenance; no evolution signal\n   113→\n   114→Bug and feedback runs are the primary evolution drivers. Features and\n   115→enhancements provide background context but don't typically trigger changes.\n   116→Classification happens via LLM inference on the prompt text — no explicit\n   117→`--type` flag needed from the user.\n   118→\n   119→### SQLite Schema Additions\n   120→\n   121→```sql\n   122→-- Add project scoping to runs\n   123→ALTER TABLE runs ADD COLUMN project_dir TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '';\n   124→\n   125→-- Extend step_executions with captured data\n   126→ALTER TABLE step_executions ADD COLUMN prompt_text TEXT;\n   127→ALTER TABLE step_executions ADD COLUMN agent_output TEXT;\n   128→ALTER TABLE step_executions ADD COLUMN attempt_number INTEGER DEFAULT 1;\n   129→\n   130→-- Track evolution passes\n   131→CREATE TABLE evolution_log (\n   132→    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n   133→    project_dir TEXT NOT NULL,\n   134→    workflow_name TEXT NOT NULL,\n   135→    trigger_run_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n   136→    created_at DATETIME NOT NULL,\n   137→    classification TEXT,\n   138→    changes_json TEXT NOT NULL,\n   139→    knowledge_delta TEXT\n   140→);\n   141→```\n   142→\n   143→### On-Disk Evolution State\n   144→\n   145→```\n   146→.cloche/\n   147→  evolution/\n   148→    log.jsonl                   # append-only audit trail (one JSON object per line)\n   149→    knowledge/\n   150→      develop.md                # ACE-style knowledge base for 'develop' workflow\n   151→    snapshots/\n   152→      <timestamp>-<filename>    # pre-change backups for revert\n   153→```\n   154→\n   155→## Pipeline Stages\n   156→\n   157→### Stage 1: Collector\n   158→\n   159→Triggers after every run completion. Gathers:\n   160→\n   161→1. All runs for this project+workflow since the last evolution pass (tracked via\n   162→   `evolution_log.trigger_run_id`)\n   163→2. The accumulated knowledge base (`knowledge/<workflow>.md`)\n   164→3. Current prompt files referenced by the workflow\n   165→4. The current `.cloche` workflow DSL file\n   166→5. Runs classified as \"bug\" or \"feedback\" carry more weight in analysis\n   167→\n   168→If there are no new runs since the last evolution, the pipeline short-circuits.\n   169→\n   170→### Stage 2: Classifier (LLM)\n   171→\n   172→For each unclassified run, the Classifier examines the run prompt and assigns a\n   173→category. The classification is stored in the run record (SQLite) for use by the\n   174→Reflector and for future queries.\n   175→\n   176→### Stage 3: Reflector (LLM)\n   177→\n   178→The Reflector examines execution traces and extracts structured lessons. It\n   179→receives the collected run data (step results, failure logs, retry counts), the\n   180→current knowledge base, and the current prompts and workflow.\n   181→\n   182→It produces delta entries — structured lessons:\n   183→\n   184→```json\n   185→{\n   186→  \"lessons\": [\n   187→    {\n   188→      \"id\": \"lesson-20260224-001\",\n   189→      \"category\": \"prompt_improvement\",\n   190→      \"target\": \"prompts/implement.md\",\n   191→      \"insight\": \"Agent consistently produces unsanitized HTML output in form handlers. 4 of last 6 bug-type runs involved XSS.\",\n   192→      \"suggested_action\": \"Add explicit rule: always sanitize user inputs with html.EscapeString() before template rendering\",\n   193→      \"evidence\": [\"run-abc\", \"run-def\", \"run-ghi\", \"run-jkl\"],\n   194→      \"confidence\": \"high\"\n   195→    },\n   196→    {\n   197→      \"id\": \"lesson-20260224-002\",\n   198→      \"category\": \"new_step\",\n   199→      \"step_type\": \"script\",\n   200→      \"insight\": \"No static security analysis in workflow. Security bugs only caught by user reports post-deployment.\",\n   201→      \"suggested_action\": \"Add gosec script step after test, wire failures to fix\",\n   202→      \"evidence\": [\"run-abc\", \"run-def\"],\n   203→      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n   204→    }\n   205→  ]\n   206→}\n   207→```\n   208→\n   209→Confidence levels (high/medium/low) are based on evidence count and pattern\n   210→consistency. Only lessons meeting the configured minimum confidence proceed to\n   211→the executor branches.\n   212→\n   213→### Stage 4: Executor Branches\n   214→\n   215→Based on each lesson's `category`, it routes to one of three branches.\n   216→\n   217→#### Branch A: Prompt Curator (LLM + deterministic dedup)\n   218→\n   219→Handles `prompt_improvement` lessons.\n   220→\n   221→- Receives the current prompt file content and the lesson\n   222→- ACE-style curation: merges the lesson into the prompt as a structured\n   223→  bullet/rule\n   224→- Deduplication: checks for semantic overlap with existing bullets; if a lesson\n   225→  refines an existing bullet, it updates in place rather than appending\n   226→- Code-fence stripping: LLM responses are cleaned of markdown code fences\n   227→  (` ``` `) before writing, extracting only the content between fences. This\n   228→  prevents meta-commentary or formatting artifacts from leaking into prompt files.\n   229→- Conversational response validation: after stripping code fences, the output is\n   230→  checked for conversational markers (e.g. \"I need write permission\", \"Here is\n   231→  the updated prompt:\", \"Could you grant access\"). If the LLM returned\n   232→  meta-conversation text instead of prompt content, the curator falls back to\n   233→  appending the lesson directly as a structured bullet rather than trusting the\n   234→  LLM output. This prevents prompt file corruption when the LLM produces\n   235→  interactive-style responses.\n   236→- Output: the modified prompt file content, written to disk\n   237→\n   238→#### Branch B: Script Generator (LLM)\n   239→\n   240→Handles `new_step` lessons where step_type is \"script\" or \"agent\".\n   241→\n   242→- Receives the lesson describing what check or analysis is needed\n   243→- Generates a script file (shell, Python, etc.) implementing the check, or a\n   244→  prompt file for agent steps\n   245→- Script/prompt is written to the project directory (e.g.,\n   246→  `scripts/security-scan.sh` or `prompts/review.md`)\n   247→- Output: the file path and content\n   248→\n   249→#### Branch C: DSL Mutator (deterministic Go code)\n   250→\n   251→Handles structural workflow changes. Receives structured proposals and applies\n   252→them to the `.cloche` workflow file. Four operations:\n   253→\n   254→**Add Step Definition:**\n   255→```json\n   256→{\n   257→  \"op\": \"add_step\",\n   258→  \"name\": \"security-scan\",\n   259→  \"type\": \"script\",\n   260→  \"config\": {\n   261→    \"run\": \"gosec ./...\",\n   262→    \"results\": [\"success\", \"fail\"]\n   263→  }\n   264→}\n   265→```\n   266→\n   267→Parses the workflow file, inserts the step definition, serializes back.\n   268→\n   269→**Add Wiring:**\n   270→```json\n   271→{\n   272→  \"op\": \"add_wire\",\n   273→  \"wires\": [\n   274→    {\"from\": \"test\", \"result\": \"success\", \"to\": \"security-scan\"},\n   275→    {\"from\": \"security-scan\", \"result\": \"fail\", \"to\": \"fix\"}\n   276→  ]\n   277→}\n   278→```\n   279→\n   280→Appends wires to the wiring section.\n   281→\n   282→**Rewire Result:**\n   283→```json\n   284→{\n   285→  \"op\": \"rewire_result\",\n   286→  \"from\": \"test\",\n   287→  \"result\": \"success\",\n   288→  \"old_to\": \"done\",\n   289→  \"new_to\": \"security-scan\"\n   290→}\n   291→```\n   292→\n   293→Changes the target of an existing wire. Used by the orchestrator when inserting\n   294→a new step into the graph: it finds a wire pointing to `done`, rewires it to\n   295→the new step, then wires the new step's results to terminals. This splices the\n   296→new step into the existing flow rather than creating a disconnected node.\n   297→\n   298→**Update Collect:**\n   299→```json\n   300→{\n   301→  \"op\": \"update_collect\",\n   302→  \"collect_target\": \"done\",\n   303→  \"add_conditions\": [\n   304→    {\"step\": \"security-scan\", \"result\": \"success\"}\n   305→  ]\n   306→}\n   307→```\n   308→\n   309→Finds the matching `collect` clause and adds the new condition.\n   310→\n   311→**Validation gate:** After any mutation, the mutator calls\n   312→`domain.Workflow.Validate()` on the result. If validation fails, the mutation is\n   313→rejected, the original file is preserved, and the failure is logged.\n   314→\n   315→**DSL Serializer:** The mutator requires a round-trip-preserving serializer —\n   316→parse into an AST that retains comments and whitespace, modify the AST, serialize\n   317→back. This preserves user formatting and comments.\n   318→\n   319→Branches B and C often fire together — a new script step needs both the script\n   320→file (B) and the DSL wiring (C).\n   321→\n   322→### Stage 5: Audit Logger\n   323→\n   324→After all changes are applied:\n   325→\n   326→1. **Snapshot** — copies pre-change versions of all modified files to\n   327→   `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/`\n   328→2. **Log** — appends a JSONL entry to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl` and inserts\n   329→   into the `evolution_log` SQLite table\n   330→3. **Knowledge base update** — appends the Reflector's lessons to\n   331→   `knowledge/<workflow>.md`, runs deduplication/refinement\n   332→\n   333→## Knowledge Base Structure\n   334→\n   335→The knowledge base is an ACE-style structured document — itemized bullets with\n   336→metadata, not prose. Each bullet tracks usefulness over time:\n   337→\n   338→```markdown\n   339→# Knowledge Base: develop workflow\n   340→\n   341→## Prompt Insights\n   342→\n   343→- **[P001]** (applied: 3, helpful: 2, stale: 0) Always sanitize user inputs\n   344→  with html.EscapeString() before template rendering. XSS vulnerabilities\n   345→  were recurring in form handlers.\n   346→  _Evidence: run-abc, run-def, run-ghi, run-jkl_\n   347→\n   348→- **[P002]** (applied: 1, helpful: 1, stale: 0) Use goimports ordering for\n   349→  imports. Lint step flags this in ~60% of runs.\n   350→  _Evidence: run-mno, run-pqr_\n   351→\n   352→## Workflow Insights\n   353→\n   354→- **[W001]** (applied: 1, helpful: 1, stale: 0) Added gosec security scan\n   355→  step. Catches static security issues before deployment.\n   356→  _Evidence: run-abc, run-def_\n   357→\n   358→## Failure Patterns\n   359→\n   360→- **[F001]** (occurrences: 8) Test timeout failures correlate with database\n   361→  connection setup. Usually resolves on retry.\n   362→  _Action: none (transient)_\n   363→\n   364→- **[F002]** (occurrences: 4) Valgrind reports unfreed memory in request\n   365→  handlers. Consistent pattern — agent needs explicit reminder about cleanup\n   366→  in defer/finally blocks.\n   367→  _Action: prompt update P001 applied_\n   368→```\n   369→\n   370→The `applied`/`helpful`/`stale` counters enable future refinement. If a lesson\n   371→is applied but the same failure keeps occurring, it can be revised or removed.\n   372→\n   373→## Trigger Logic\n   374→\n   375→### When Evolution Runs\n   376→\n   377→The pipeline triggers in the daemon after every workflow run completes (success\n   378→or failure). Smart throttling prevents waste:\n   379→\n   380→- **Debounce:** If runs complete in rapid succession (parallel runs on the same\n   381→  project), wait a configurable period (default 30s) after the last completion\n   382→  before triggering. This batches multiple runs into one analysis pass.\n   383→- **Mutex:** If an evolution pass is already in progress for this\n   384→  project+workflow, skip. The next run completion will pick up the slack.\n   385→- **No-op detection:** If the Reflector finds nothing actionable (clean feature\n   386→  runs, no patterns), the pipeline logs \"no changes\" and exits without firing\n   387→  the executor branches.\n   388→\n   389→### History Window\n   390→\n   391→The Collector gathers all runs since the last evolution pass (tracked via\n   392→`evolution_log.trigger_run_id`). The knowledge base provides the long-term\n   393→memory — once raw runs are analyzed, their lessons persist in the knowledge base\n   394→even as the raw data ages out. This gives the system both recency (raw run data)\n   395→and continuity (accumulated knowledge).\n   396→\n   397→## Protocol Changes\n   398→\n   399→### gRPC (CLI to Daemon)\n   400→\n   401→```protobuf\n   402→message RunRequest {\n   403→  string workflow = 1;\n   404→  string prompt = 2;\n   405→  string project_dir = 3;   // NEW\n   406→}\n   407→```\n   408→\n   409→### Status Protocol (Agent to Daemon)\n   410→\n   411→```protobuf\n   412→message StepStarted {\n   413→  string step_name = 1;\n   414→  string prompt_text = 2;    // NEW: assembled prompt\n   415→}\n   416→\n   417→message StepCompleted {\n   418→  string step_name = 1;\n   419→  string result = 2;\n   420→  string agent_output = 3;   // NEW: LLM response\n   421→  int32 attempt_number = 4;  // NEW\n   422→}\n   423→```\n   424→\n   425→### Prompt Adapter Changes\n   426→\n   427→The prompt adapter captures the assembled prompt text before invoking the agent\n   428→and the agent's stdout after it returns. Both are forwarded to the daemon via\n   429→the status protocol. No changes to prompt assembly logic — the evolution system\n   430→modifies prompt files on disk, and the existing `file()` mechanism picks up\n   431→changes on the next run.\n   432→\n   433→## Configuration\n   434→\n   435→Per-project in `.cloche/config`:\n   436→\n   437→```toml\n   438→[evolution]\n   439→enabled = true                # master switch\n   440→debounce_seconds = 30         # wait after last run before analyzing\n   441→min_confidence = \"medium\"     # minimum lesson confidence to act on\n   442→max_prompt_bullets = 50       # cap on knowledge bullets per prompt\n   443→```\n   444→\n   445→Evolution is enabled by default. Users can disable it per-project for static\n   446→workflows.\n   447→\n   448→## Future Work (Out of Scope)\n   449→\n   450→- **Step removal/mutation** — modifying or removing existing step definitions\n   451→  (higher risk, needs careful design around backwards compatibility)\n   452→- **`cloche evolve --revert <evo-id>`** — automated revert from snapshots\n   453→- **Helpfulness tracking** — automatically detecting whether applied lessons\n   454→  actually reduced failure rates, and pruning unhelpful ones\n   455→- **Cross-project learning** — sharing knowledge base insights across projects\n   456→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01YNtMJ1cKQdPtGDZdFVC9hG","session_id":"41846d44-0d79-434c-81b9-81f7289ac468","uuid":"88486548-82a7-4db9-af99-5f417a6ced53"}
