{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YNtMJ1cKQdPtGDZdFVC9hG","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile my findings. I have thoroughly searched the workspace for documentation files mentioning the requested terms. Here's my comprehensive report:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've found comprehensive documentation across the workspace that discusses evolution, knowledge bases, auditing, and related features. Here are all the relevant files and excerpts:\n\n---\n\n## Files Found with Requested Terms\n\n### 1. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`**\n**Core evolution system design document**\n\nKey excerpts:\n- **Evolution Overview (lines 1-14)**: The self-evolution system analyzes workflow run history and user feedback to automatically improve prompts, add validation steps, and refine workflows over time.\n- **Architecture (lines 19-72)**: Multi-stage pipeline with Collector, Classifier, Reflector, and three executor branches (Prompt Curator, Script Generator, DSL Mutator), plus Audit Logger.\n- **Knowledge Base Structure (lines 333-368)**: ACE-style structured document with itemized bullets tracking usefulness over time (applied, helpful, stale counters). Example shows metadata tags like `[P001]`, `[P002]` with evidence links.\n- **Data Collection (lines 90-141)**: Captures assembled prompts, agent stdout, run classification (bug/feedback/feature/enhancement/chore), retry counts per step, and project directory. New SQLite schema adds `project_dir`, `prompt_text`, `agent_output`, `attempt_number` to runs and step_executions.\n- **Evolution Triggers (lines 373-395)**: Pipeline triggers after every run completion with smart throttling (debounce, mutex, no-op detection). Handles history windows based on last evolution pass.\n- **Configuration (lines 433-446)**: Per-project settings in `.cloche/config`:\n  - `enabled = true`\n  - `debounce_seconds = 30`\n  - `min_confidence = \"medium\"`\n  - `max_prompt_bullets = 50`\n- **Deduplication Logic (lines 217-237)**: Prompt Curator uses semantic deduplication to check for overlap with existing bullets; if a lesson refines an existing bullet, it updates in place rather than appending. Includes code-fence stripping and conversational response validation.\n\n### 2. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md`**\n**Step-by-step implementation plan** (67KB)\n\nThis document contains:\n- Task-by-task implementation breakdown\n- Protobuf message definitions for new signals\n- SQL schema extensions\n- File I/O patterns for knowledge base and audit logging\n- Go interfaces for evolution components\n- Integration points with daemon and agent\n\n### 3. **`/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`**\n**User-facing documentation**\n\nRelevant sections:\n- **Prompt Assembly (lines 217-226)**: Explains how prompts are assembled from template, user request, optional validation output (via `feedback = \"true\"`), and result selection.\n- **Prompt Hygiene section in SAFETY.md**: Discusses separating trusted prompt templates from untrusted user requests to prevent injection attacks.\n\n### 4. **`/workspace/docs/SAFETY.md`**\n**Security guidance**\n\nKey points:\n- **Prompt Hygiene (lines 180-199)**: Separates trusted prompts (in `.cloche/prompts/`) from untrusted external content (task descriptions, issue bodies). Cloche's prompt assembly concatenates both, requiring careful prompt design.\n- **Validation with `feedback` (lines 196-199)**: The `feedback = \"true\"` step config includes previous output logs; these can be an injection surface if logs contain untrusted data.\n\n### 5. **`/workspace/docs/workflows.md`**\n**Workflow DSL specification**\n\nRelated to evolution:\n- **Wire Output Mappings (lines 134-166)**: Steps can extract values from JSON output and inject as env vars into targets. Relevant for evolution's DSL mutation operations.\n- **Wiring is separate (lines 127-129)**: Explicitly notes that wiring separation enables inserting new steps without modifying existing ones — the foundation for evolution's rewiring strategy.\n\n### 6. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md`**\n**Project configuration format**\n\nRelevant sections:\n- **Evolution Configuration (lines 26-31)**:\n  ```toml\n  [evolution]\n  enabled           = true\n  debounce_seconds  = 30\n  min_confidence    = \"medium\"\n  max_prompt_bullets = 50\n  ```\n\n### 7. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-versioning-design.md`**\n**Version tracking for evolved projects**\n\nDetails:\n- **Version File (lines 15-24)**: Plain integer stored in `.cloche/version`, created with value `1` on `cloche init`. Incremented by daemon when evolution pipeline produces changes.\n- **Increment Rule (lines 26-38)**: After audit stage, if changes detected, increment version atomically. `LoadVersion()` reads version, defaults to 1 if missing.\n- **Integration (lines 51-74)**: Version exposed in project info page, included in evolution audit log (though not duplicated there).\n\n### 8. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md`**\n**Init command updates**\n\nIncludes:\n- **Files Created (lines 46-64)**: `.cloche/config.toml`, `.cloche/version` (initialized to \"1\"), `host.cloche`, `scripts/prepare-prompt.sh`\n- **Evolution Settings (lines 77-81)**: Default config.toml includes evolution section with enabled=true, debounce_seconds=30, min_confidence=\"medium\", max_prompt_bullets=50\n\n### 9. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`**\n**Web UI for project management**\n\nEvolution-related sections:\n- **Project Info Panel (lines 69-112)**: Displays project version (sourced from `.cloche/version` as `v3`), prompt file contents with git commit history\n- **Workflow View (lines 139-227)**: Displays current workflow state (not evolution history)\n\n### 10. **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`**\n**High-level system architecture**\n\nFoundat