{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019s59dDPmopMdT8Uepnsiq4","type":"tool_result","content":"   320→file (B) and the DSL wiring (C).\n   321→\n   322→### Stage 5: Audit Logger\n   323→\n   324→After all changes are applied:\n   325→\n   326→1. **Snapshot** — copies pre-change versions of all modified files to\n   327→   `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/`\n   328→2. **Log** — appends a JSONL entry to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl` and inserts\n   329→   into the `evolution_log` SQLite table\n   330→3. **Knowledge base update** — appends the Reflector's lessons to\n   331→   `knowledge/<workflow>.md`, runs deduplication/refinement\n   332→\n   333→## Knowledge Base Structure\n   334→\n   335→The knowledge base is an ACE-style structured document — itemized bullets with\n   336→metadata, not prose. Each bullet tracks usefulness over time:\n   337→\n   338→```markdown\n   339→# Knowledge Base: develop workflow\n   340→\n   341→## Prompt Insights\n   342→\n   343→- **[P001]** (applied: 3, helpful: 2, stale: 0) Always sanitize user inputs\n   344→  with html.EscapeString() before template rendering. XSS vulnerabilities\n   345→  were recurring in form handlers.\n   346→  _Evidence: run-abc, run-def, run-ghi, run-jkl_\n   347→\n   348→- **[P002]** (applied: 1, helpful: 1, stale: 0) Use goimports ordering for\n   349→  imports. Lint step flags this in ~60% of runs.\n   350→  _Evidence: run-mno, run-pqr_\n   351→\n   352→## Workflow Insights\n   353→\n   354→- **[W001]** (applied: 1, helpful: 1, stale: 0) Added gosec security scan\n   355→  step. Catches static security issues before deployment.\n   356→  _Evidence: run-abc, run-def_\n   357→\n   358→## Failure Patterns\n   359→\n   360→- **[F001]** (occurrences: 8) Test timeout failures correlate with database\n   361→  connection setup. Usually resolves on retry.\n   362→  _Action: none (transient)_\n   363→\n   364→- **[F002]** (occurrences: 4) Valgrind reports unfreed memory in request\n   365→  handlers. Consistent pattern — agent needs explicit reminder about cleanup\n   366→  in defer/finally blocks.\n   367→  _Action: prompt update P001 applied_\n   368→```\n   369→\n   370→The `applied`/`helpful`/`stale` counters enable future refinement. If a lesson\n   371→is applied but the same failure keeps occurring, it can be revised or removed.\n   372→\n   373→## Trigger Logic\n   374→\n   375→### When Evolution Runs\n   376→\n   377→The pipeline triggers in the daemon after every workflow run completes (success\n   378→or failure). Smart throttling prevents waste:\n   379→\n   380→- **Debounce:** If runs complete in rapid succession (parallel runs on the same\n   381→  project), wait a configurable period (default 30s) after the last completion\n   382→  before triggering. This batches multiple runs into one analysis pass.\n   383→- **Mutex:** If an evolution pass is already in progress for this\n   384→  project+workflow, skip. The next run completion will pick up the slack.\n   385→- **No-op detection:** If the Reflector finds nothing actionable (clean feature\n   386→  runs, no patterns), the pipeline logs \"no changes\" and exits without firing\n   387→  the executor branches.\n   388→\n   389→### History Window\n   390→\n   391→The Collector gathers all runs since the last evolution pass (tracked via\n   392→`evolution_log.trigger_run_id`). The knowledge base provides the long-term\n   393→memory — once raw runs are analyzed, their lessons persist in the knowledge base\n   394→even as the raw data ages out. This gives the system both recency (raw run data)\n   395→and continuity (accumulated knowledge).\n   396→\n   397→## Protocol Changes\n   398→\n   399→### gRPC (CLI to Daemon)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"41846d44-0d79-434c-81b9-81f7289ac468","uuid":"ef6bfc1e-ab86-4d99-aac3-4e025c548efe","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md","content":"file (B) and the DSL wiring (C).\n\n### Stage 5: Audit Logger\n\nAfter all changes are applied:\n\n1. **Snapshot** — copies pre-change versions of all modified files to\n   `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/`\n2. **Log** — appends a JSONL entry to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl` and inserts\n   into the `evolution_log` SQLite table\n3. **Knowledge base update** — appends the Reflector's lessons to\n   `knowledge/<workflow>.md`, runs deduplication/refinement\n\n## Knowledge Base Structure\n\nThe knowledge base is an ACE-style structured document — itemized bullets with\nmetadata, not prose. Each bullet tracks usefulness over time:\n\n```markdown\n# Knowledge Base: develop workflow\n\n## Prompt Insights\n\n- **[P001]** (applied: 3, helpful: 2, stale: 0) Always sanitize user inputs\n  with html.EscapeString() before template rendering. XSS vulnerabilities\n  were recurring in form handlers.\n  _Evidence: run-abc, run-def, run-ghi, run-jkl_\n\n- **[P002]** (applied: 1, helpful: 1, stale: 0) Use goimports ordering for\n  imports. Lint step flags this in ~60% of runs.\n  _Evidence: run-mno, run-pqr_\n\n## Workflow Insights\n\n- **[W001]** (applied: 1, helpful: 1, stale: 0) Added gosec security scan\n  step. Catches static security issues before deployment.\n  _Evidence: run-abc, run-def_\n\n## Failure Patterns\n\n- **[F001]** (occurrences: 8) Test timeout failures correlate with database\n  connection setup. Usually resolves on retry.\n  _Action: none (transient)_\n\n- **[F002]** (occurrences: 4) Valgrind reports unfreed memory in request\n  handlers. Consistent pattern — agent needs explicit reminder about cleanup\n  in defer/finally blocks.\n  _Action: prompt update P001 applied_\n```\n\nThe `applied`/`helpful`/`stale` counters enable future refinement. If a lesson\nis applied but the same failure keeps occurring, it can be revised or removed.\n\n## Trigger Logic\n\n### When Evolution Runs\n\nThe pipeline triggers in the daemon after every workflow run completes (success\nor failure). Smart throttling prevents waste:\n\n- **Debounce:** If runs complete in rapid succession (parallel runs on the same\n  project), wait a configurable period (default 30s) after the last completion\n  before triggering. This batches multiple runs into one analysis pass.\n- **Mutex:** If an evolution pass is already in progress for this\n  project+workflow, skip. The next run completion will pick up the slack.\n- **No-op detection:** If the Reflector finds nothing actionable (clean feature\n  runs, no patterns), the pipeline logs \"no changes\" and exits without firing\n  the executor branches.\n\n### History Window\n\nThe Collector gathers all runs since the last evolution pass (tracked via\n`evolution_log.trigger_run_id`). The knowledge base provides the long-term\nmemory — once raw runs are analyzed, their lessons persist in the knowledge base\neven as the raw data ages out. This gives the system both recency (raw run data)\nand continuity (accumulated knowledge).\n\n## Protocol Changes\n\n### gRPC (CLI to Daemon)","numLines":80,"startLine":320,"totalLines":456}}}
